  "transcript": "Google just dropped Disco, their new AI browser that basically combines googling with vibe coding. And it works by using a new feature called GenTabs. It basically scans all your open browser tabs, then spots patterns in your browsing, and instantly turns them into task specific custom mini apps. So instead of switch switching between 20 different pages, Disco scans them all and then builds you a single interactive dashboard. For example, if you ask for travel tips, it'll create a full trip planner app with interactive maps and hotel price comparisons. Ask about space and it'll generate you three d solar systems you can actually explore and then quiz yourself on. Right now, it's strictly invite only. So if you want the link to try it, just comment Google down below and I'll send it to you directly.",
